2 16S sequencing results

16S rRNA amplicon sequencing (minimum 20,000 reads per sample) ## Summary sequencing results

# read Sample Sheet file path
SSlist=fread(paste0(M3folder_loc, sample_sheet_list_fp), header=FALSE)

# read each file and add to the master
all_map=NULL
for(i in 1:nrow(SSlist)){
  batch_name=as.character(SSlist[i, V1])
  ss_data=fread(paste0(M3folder_loc, as.character(SSlist[i, V2])), header=TRUE)
  # select columns
  ss_data <- ss_data[, list(Library.Barcode=Sample_ID, ReadDepth=`READ COUNT`, family)]
  # add batch name
  ss_data <- ss_data[, batch:=batch_name]
  # add to master
  all_map=rbindlist(list(all_map, ss_data))
}

# remove all 'Undetermined' (PhiX) and controls
all_map <- all_map[grepl('M3_', family)]

# remove 'family' column to avoid confusion (this family is based on tube labels)
all_map <- all_map[, family:=NULL]

# replace '-' to '_' in the sequencing batch
all_map <- all_map[, batch:=gsub('-', '_', batch)]

# add Batch 10
b10=fread(paste0(M3folder_loc, batch10_stats_fp), header=TRUE)
b10 <- unique(b10[, list(Library.Barcode=Sample_ID, ReadDepth=Total_Reads, batch='M05416_77_000000000_C29M9')])
all_map <- rbindlist(list(all_map, b10))

# plot read distribution in each batch
# add pseudocounts of 0.0001 to ReadDepth==0 samples for plotting
ggplot(data=all_map[, list(batch, RD=ifelse(ReadDepth==0, 0.0001, ReadDepth))], aes(x=batch, y=RD))+
  geom_boxplot(outlier.color='white')+
  geom_jitter(position=position_jitter(width=0.4), size=1)+
  scale_y_log10()+
  theme_bw()+ ylab('Read Depth')+
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45, hjust=1))

2.1 Asteria (CLAMPR-DADA2) results

# read DD results file path
DDreslist=mapping

# read each file and add to the master
all_cts=NULL

for(i in 1:nrow(DDreslist)){
  # record batch
  batch_name=as.character(DDreslist[i, V3])
  # read abundance table
  dd_data=fread(paste0(M3folder_loc, as.character(DDreslist[i, V5]), '400_DADA_ASVabundance_withSequence.csv'), header=TRUE)
  # remove column 'ASV' from abundance table
  dd_data <- dd_data[, ASV:=NULL]
  # convert to long format
  dd_data <- melt(dd_data, id.vars='Sequence')
  # remove 0
  dd_data <- dd_data[value!=0]
  # add batch name
  dd_data <- dd_data[, batch:=batch_name]
  # add to master
  all_cts=rbindlist(list(all_cts, dd_data))
}

# replace column name
setnames(all_cts, 'variable', 'Library.Barcode')

# replace '-' to '_' in the sequencing batch
all_cts <- all_cts[, batch:=gsub('-', '_', batch)]

3 Generate phyloseq object

Use the combined results from Asteria helper script for PS generation

# Theses combined files are now uploaded to s3: s3://sg-processing/INRD17_0415/16S_NGS/Asteria/200312_ASVdata8_updateAsteria/
# Abundance table
abund <- read.csv(paste0(M3folder_loc, DDreslist_folder, "INRD17_0415_combinedRuns_strainCollapsed_abundance.csv")) %>% reshape2::melt(., id.var = "bin")

# Get the meta_data and aggregate by biospecimen
abund <- merge(abund, metaDT_ofs[, c("Library.Barcode", "Biospecimen.Barcode","Sequencing.run.ID..OmicsFileSet.")], by.x="variable", by.y = "Library.Barcode", all.x = T) %>% setDT(.)

# L18007742 L18007743 - no biospecimen barcode, and do not exsit in KB but in the sequencing run, remove 
# L18007742 L18007743 are from batch "M02273_20_000000000_BTF24" (Batch123re2_MS039), they are "NegCtrl, KF032 NegCtrl 18_0415" and "NTC 16S046 PCR NTC" respectively. However, they were not recorded in KB. The total reads for each of them are 0, and 6 reads. 

abund <- abund[!is.na(Biospecimen.Barcode)]
# Remove samples that do not pass min_postDD
pass_min_postDD_cts <- abund[Biospecimen.Barcode %in% (abund[, list(post_DD_cts=sum(value)), by='Biospecimen.Barcode'][post_DD_cts>min_postDD]$Biospecimen.Barcode)]

pass_min_postDD_cts <- pass_min_postDD_cts[,list(co_value = sum(value)), by = list(Biospecimen.Barcode, bin)] %>% dcast(., bin ~ Biospecimen.Barcode, value.var = "co_value") %>% setDT(.)
# number of samples passed
ncol(pass_min_postDD_cts)-1
## [1] 668
# also remove the bins which are classified as "ERCC-00025_PCR" or "ERCC-00154_PCR"
OTU <- pass_min_postDD_cts[!grepl("ERCC", bin)]
OTU <- data.frame(OTU)
row.names(OTU) <- OTU$bin
OTU$bin <- NULL

# Get the taxa table
TAX <- read.csv(paste0(M3folder_loc, DDreslist_folder, "INRD17_0415_combinedRuns_strainCollapsed_taxtable.csv"), row.names = 1, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
TAX <- TAX[!grepl("ERCC", row.names(TAX)),]
TAX$ss_id <- NULL
TAX$ref_ASV <- NULL
TAX <- tax_table(as(TAX, "matrix"))

# Get sample data
# Add phenotype column to meta data
metaDT_b$phenotype <- as.character(lapply(strsplit(as.character(metaDT_b$Host.Name), split='_'), '[', 2))
# Get the runID per biospecimen
seqruns=unique(abund[, list(Biospecimen.Barcode, Sequencing.run.ID..OmicsFileSet.)])[, list(Sequencing.run.ID..OmicsFileSet._collapsed=paste0(Sequencing.run.ID..OmicsFileSet., collapse=';')), by=Biospecimen.Barcode]
pass_min_postDD_cts_meta <- merge(metaDT_b, seqruns, by='Biospecimen.Barcode')
pass_min_postDD_cts_meta <- pass_min_postDD_cts_meta[pass_min_postDD_cts_meta$Biospecimen.Barcode %in% colnames(OTU),]
colnames(pass_min_postDD_cts_meta) <- gsub("..Biospecimen.","", colnames(pass_min_postDD_cts_meta))
# metadata
SAMPLEDATA <- data.frame(pass_min_postDD_cts_meta)
row.names(SAMPLEDATA) <- SAMPLEDATA$Biospecimen.Barcode

# phyloseq object
ps_not_norm = phyloseq(otu_table(OTU, taxa_are_rows=TRUE), TAX, sample_data(SAMPLEDATA))
ps_not_norm
## phyloseq-class experiment-level object
## otu_table()   OTU Table:         [ 5013 taxa and 668 samples ]
## sample_data() Sample Data:       [ 668 samples by 364 sample variables ]
## tax_table()   Taxonomy Table:    [ 5013 taxa by 8 taxonomic ranks ]
#and now save this object
saveRDS(ps_not_norm, file=paste(output_data, "ps_not_norm_pass_min_postDD.rds", sep=""))

3.1 Age filtering of the Phyloseq Object

  • Filter: ‘Age..months.’ >23 but keep ‘Host.Name’ %in% c(‘004_N’, ‘065_N’)
  • Use the ps_age_filter(rds_path, output_dir) function
# create the output folder
dir.create(paste0(output_data, "age_filtered_PS_objects"))
# run the filter and save RDS
ps_age_filter(paste(output_data, "ps_not_norm_pass_min_postDD.rds", sep=""), paste0(output_data, "age_filtered_PS_objects"))

3.2 Get complete families

# First read in 
ps_not_norm_age_filter <- readRDS(paste0(output_data,"age_filtered_PS_objects/ps_not_norm_pass_min_postDD_age_filtered.rds"))

complete_families=sort(unique(sample_data(ps_not_norm_age_filter)$Family.group.ID))[table(sample_data(ps_not_norm_age_filter)$Family.group.ID) == 6]
length(complete_families)
## [1] 77
ps_not_norm_age_filter_comp <- prune_samples(row.names(sample_data(ps_not_norm_age_filter)[sample_data(ps_not_norm_age_filter)$Family.group.ID %in% complete_families]), ps_not_norm_age_filter)
